    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1140/246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-30T21:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 30, 1918—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 31—6:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. For <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">Polk</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_AG1">Auchincloss</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1"
                        >Colonel House</persName> wishes <persName corresp="#p_MSE1"
                        >Mezes</persName> to be asked to send him a cable advising him of the
                    progress and difficulties of “Inquiry” since his departure. He wishes further to
                    be fully advised regarding this work by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
